    <p>Happy (not) Christmas ponyfolks! Spoiler: It&#8217;s another episode with Starlight Glimmer in it! </p>
    <h4>The People&#8217;s Ponydrome</h4>
    <p>In the past we&#8217;ve dictated what you should watch and listen to like illiberal, bourgeoisie pigs. Well no more! Using state-of-the-art computing technology, we have created a system where <em>you</em>, the common proletariat worker, can determine what you want to see (and by extension everybody else). </p>
    <p>DISCLAIMER: This system is experimental. It might not work, and heck, giving people unmoderated reign over a public broadcasting service is probably a really bad idea&#8230; We&#8217;ll see how it works out. </p>
    <h4>Every day we&#8217;re <del>rafflin&#8217;</del> auctionin&#8217;</h4>
    <p>The meets have been running for nearly four years (did we mention it&#8217;s been nearly four years?) and in that time we&#8217;ve built up a lot of what can only be called &#8220;guff&#8221;. Uncollected competition prizes, unclaimed lost property and leftover merch makes up a significant quantity of things clogging up Kim&#8217;s flat. Let&#8217;s get rid of it! </p>
